%N A103279 Array read by antidiagonals, generated by the matrix M = [1,1,1;1,N,1;1,1,1].
%C A103279 Consider the matrix M = [1,1,1;1,N,1;1,1,1]; Characteristic polynomial of M is x^3 + (-N - 2)*x^2 + (2*N - 2)*x.
%C A103279 Now (M^n)[1,1] is equivalent to the recursion a(1) = 1, a(2) = 3, a(n) = (N+2)a(n-1)+(2N-2)a(n-2). (This also holds for negative N and fractional N.)
%C A103279 a(n+1)/a(n) converges to the upper root of the characteristic polynomial ((N + 2) + sqrt((N - 2)^2 + 8))/2 for n to infinity.
%C A103279 Columns of array follow the polynomials:
%C A103279 1,
%C A103279 3,
%C A103279 N + 8,
%C A103279 N^2 + 4*N + 22,
%C A103279 N^3 + 4*N^2 + 16*N + 60,
%C A103279 N^4 + 4*N^3 + 18*N^2 + 56*N + 164,
%C A103279 N^5 + 4*N^4 + 20*N^3 + 68*N^2 + 188*N + 448,
%C A103279 N^6 + 4*N^5 + 22*N^4 + 80*N^3 + 248*N^2 + 608*N + 1224,
%C A103279 N^7 + 4*N^6 + 24*N^5 + 92*N^4 + 312*N^3 + 864*N^2 + 1920*N + 3344,
%C A103279 N^8 + 4*N^7 + 26*N^6 + 104*N^5 + 380*N^4 + 1152*N^3 + 2928*N^2 + 5952*N + 9136,
%C A103279 etc.
%F A103279 T(N, 1)=1, T(N, 2)=3, T(N, n)=(N+2)*T(N, n-1)-(2*N-2)*T(N, n-2).
%e A103279 Array begins:
%e A103279 1,3,8,22,60,164,448,1224,3344,9136,...
